hopobject.body: What's the exchange rate for euros? edpharmacyonline.com By late afternoon, helped by the attractions of the Victoria Monument fountains on the hottest day of the year in the capital, the crowds outside Buckingham Palace had swelled into the hundreds as excited well-wishers, tourists and curious passersby awaited the official announcement that a future monarch had been born. Some had brought champagne, many others had Union flags ready to be waved.
